data.name: textBox1.Text
data.value: Lyceum of the Philippines University (LPU) is a private, non-sectarian, coeducational higher education institution located in Intramuros, Manila, Philippines. It was founded in 1952 by Dr. José P. Laurel, the third president of the Republic of the Philippines. LPU has six campuses in the Philippines, located in Manila, Makati, Cavite, Batangas, Laguna, and Davao.
